1)  Description of Target Image

•  Block Count and Layers  
   –  There are 6 total blocks.  
   –  They stack in 4 vertical layers:  
     1st layer (bottom): 2 yellow rectangular blocks forming an “L” shape on the floor  
     2nd layer: 1 red curved block centered above the front yellow block  
     3rd layer: 1 green rectangular block spanning left‐to‐right on top of the red block  
     4th layer (top): 2 blue cubes side by side  

•  Spatial Relationships  
   –  On the bottom layer, one yellow rectangle is oriented left‐to‐right (front).  The second yellow rectangle is oriented front‐to‐back (behind/right).  Together they make an “L” shaped footprint.  
   –  The red curved block sits directly on the front yellow block and faces outward so its curved cavity opens at the front.  
   –  A single green rectangular block rests on top of the red curved block, running left‐to‐right.  
   –  Finally, two blue cubes sit side by side on top of that green block, forming the highest layer.  

2)  Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on the exact color/shape/orientation in the dictionary images (no re‐orientations allowed), the needed blocks and their indices are:

•  Yellow rectangular block (horizontal, left‐to‐right) → Index 14  
•  Yellow rectangular block (horizontal, front‐to‐back) → Index 16  
•  Red curved block (curved opening facing front) → Index 3  
•  Green rectangular block (horizontal, left‐to‐right) → Index 11  
•  Blue cube (used twice) → Index 8 (×2)  

3)  Assembly Order

Below is one suitable step‐by‐step assembly sequence:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 14  
  Step2: Move block with index 16  
  Step3: Move block with index 3  
  Step4: Move block with index 11  
  Step5: Move block with index 8  
  Step6: Move block with index 8
}
